Both required outputs are written and validated.

**transcript.json** (152 KB): 25 iterations, 226 hypotheses (all unique IDs), 226 analyses, schema-validated.

**analysis_summary.txt** (14 KB): full narrative across all iterations.

**Key finding** — the only treatment with a real objective_response effect is venetoclax_azacitidine, and it is sharply concentrated in the subgroup
`unfit_for_intensive==1 AND npm1_mutation==1 AND tp53_mutation==0 AND complex_karyotype==0` (N=4,531: 78.6% response on ven/aza vs 15.8% off; +62.8pp; adjusted OR ≈ 21). Outside this subgroup ven/aza had no benefit (adjusted OR ≈ 0.98). TP53 and complex karyotype each completely abolish the benefit; both NPM1+ AND unfit are necessary (3-way interaction p < 1e-30). The four targeted FLT3/IDH agents (midostaurin, gilteritinib, ivosidenib, enasidenib) showed no effect on response even within their indicated mutation subgroups; 7+3 had no positive subgroup and a small detriment in CK+.
